    {
      "type": "tool_result",
      "agent": "main",
      "content": "File: node_modules/camoufox-js/README.md (71 lines) [hash:02781ffe]\n1|# camoufox-js\n2|\n3|This is the JavaScript client for Camoufox. It is a port of the Python wrapper (doesn't call the original Python scripts).\n4|\n5|## Installation\n6|\n7|```bash\n8|npm install camoufox-js\n9|```\n10|\n11|## Usage \n12|\n13|You can launch Playwright-controlled Camoufox using this package like this:\n14|\n15|```javascript\n16|import { Camoufox } from 'camoufox-js';\n17|\n18|// you might need to run `npx camoufox-js fetch` to download the browser after installing the package\n19|\n20|const browser = await Camoufox({\n21|    // custom camoufox options\n22|});\n23|            \n24|const page = await browser.newPage(); // `page` is a Playwright Page instance\n25|```\n26|\n27|Alternatively, if you want to use additional Playwright launch options, you can launch the Camoufox instance like this:\n28|\n29|```javascript\n30|import { launchOptions } from 'camoufox-js';\n31|import { firefox } from 'playwright-core';\n32|\n33|// you might need to run `npx camoufox-js fetch` to download the browser after installing the package\n34|\n35|const browser = await firefox.launch({\n36|    ...await launchOptions({ /* Camoufox options */ }),\n37|    // other Playwright options, overriding the Camoufox options\n38|});\n39|            \n40|const page = await browser.newPage(); // `page` is a Playwright Page instance\n41|```\n42|\n43|### Launching a Camoufox server\n44|\n45|Camoufox can be ran as a remote websocket server. It can be accessed from other devices, and languages other than Python supporting the Playwright API.\n46|\n47|```javascript\n48|import { launchServer } from 'camoufox-js';\n49|import { firefox } from 'playwright-core';\n50|\n51|// you might need to run `npx camoufox-js fetch` to download the browser after installing the package\n52|\n53|const server = await launchServer({ port: 8888, ws_path: '/camoufox' });\n54|const browser = await firefox.connect(server.wsEndpoint());\n55|\n56|const page = await browser.newPage();\n57|\n58|// ...\n59|// Use your browser instance as usual\n60|// ...\n61|\n62|await browser.close();  \n63|await server.close(); // Close the server when done\n64|```\n65|\n66|## More info\n67|\n68|See https://camoufox.com/ or https://github.com/daijro/camoufox for more information on Camoufox.\n69|\n70|\n71|",
